3.10	Heart_of_Gold_(Neil_Young_song)	Heart of Gold (Neil Young song)	"Heart of Gold" is a song by Canadian singer-songwriter Neil Young. Released from the 1972 album Harvest, it is so far Young's only U.S. #1 single. In Canada, it reached #1 on the RPM national singles chart for the first time on April 8, 1972, on which date Young held the top spot on both the singles and albums charts. In 2004, Rolling Stone ranked it #297 on their list of the 500 greatest songs of all time.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/31/Heart_of_Gold_by_Neal_Yound_single_cover.jpg/220px-Heart_of_Gold_by_Neal_Yound_single_cover.jpg
